<usermanual>															
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

								*SEX ROLE ORIENTATION SCALE (SRO)*
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 03-08-2017
last updated:  02-28-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-28-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

This script implements a computerized version of the SRO scale as described in:

Brogan, D. & Kutner, N.G., 1976: Measuring sex-role orientations: A normative approach. 
Journal of Marriage and The Family 38, 31-40.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
36 6-point Likert Scales, scored with 1-6 (the lower the score the more traditional the view of sex roles)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 4 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	 
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'sro_scale.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	   	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
								Scale: 1(strongly agree) - 6 (strongly disagree)
								R = automatically reversed scored questions
									
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
								question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)

(2) Summary data file: 'sro_scale_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)
								
sro_total: 						total score (Min: 36 - Max:216); 
								=> the lower the score the more traditional the view of sex roles

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
instructions can be changed under section Editable Parameters.
To change the wording of the questions, go to section QUESTIONS

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/pageinstructions:		the general instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage	

</usermanual>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

/pageinstructions:			the instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "Please answer the following questions.
"
</parameters>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
							REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS:
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0

<defaults>
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, 
script.elapsedTime, script.completed,
expressions.sro_total)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

/sro_total: 	total score (Min: 36 - Max:216); the lower the score the more traditional the view of sex roles are

<expressions>
/sro_total = radiobuttons.q1.response + radiobuttons.q2.response + radiobuttons.q3R.response + radiobuttons.q4.response +
radiobuttons.q5.response + radiobuttons.q6.response + radiobuttons.q7.response + radiobuttons.q8.response  + 
radiobuttons.q9.response + radiobuttons.q10.response + radiobuttons.q11.response + radiobuttons.q12R.response + 
radiobuttons.q13.response + radiobuttons.q14R.response + radiobuttons.q15.response + radiobuttons.q16.response + 
radiobuttons.q17R.response + radiobuttons.q18R.response + radiobuttons.q19.response + radiobuttons.q20R.response +
radiobuttons.q21R.response + radiobuttons.q22.response + radiobuttons.q23R.response + radiobuttons.q24R.response + 
radiobuttons.q25R.response + radiobuttons.q26.response + radiobuttons.q27R.response + radiobuttons.q28.response +
radiobuttons.q29.response + radiobuttons.q30.response + radiobuttons.q31R.response + radiobuttons.q32R.response +
radiobuttons.q33.response + radiobuttons.q34.response + radiobuttons.q35R.response + radiobuttons.q36R.response
</expressions>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1>
/caption = "1. It is more important for a wife to help her husband's career than to have a career herself."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2>
/caption = "2. The idea of young girls participating in Little League baseball competition is ridiculous."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3R>
/caption = "3. The relative amounts of time and energy devoted to a career on the one hand, and to home and family on the other hand, should be determined by one's personal desires and interests rather than by one's sex."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4>
/caption = "4. It is more important for a woman to keep her figure and dress becomingly than it is for a man."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5>
/caption = "5. The old saying that 'a woman's place is in the home' is still basically true and should remain true."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6>
/caption = "6. A woman should refrain from being too competitive with men and keep her peace rather than show a man he is wrong."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7>
/caption = "7. A woman whose job involves contact with the public, e.g., salesperson or teacher, should not continue to work when she is noticeably pregnant."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8>
/caption = "8. The husband should take primary responsibility for major family decisions, such as the purchase of a home or car."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q9>
/caption = "9. In groups that have both male and female members, it is appropriate that top leadership positions be held by males."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q10>
/caption = "10. Unless it is economically necessary, married women who have school-aged children should not work outside the home."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>


<radiobuttons q11>
/caption = "11. If there are two candidates for a job, one a man and the other a woman, and the woman is slightly better qualified, the job should nevertheless go to the man because he is likely to have a family to support."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q12R>
/caption = "12. Marriage is a partnership in which the wife and husband should share the economic responsibility of supporting the family."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q13>
/caption = "13. A woman should not accept a career promotion if it would require her family to move and her husband to find another job."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q14R>
/caption = "14. A married woman who chooses not to have children because she prefers to pursue her career should not feel guilty."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q15>
/caption = "15. Unless it is economically necessary, married women who have preschool-age children should not work outside the home."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q16>
/caption = "16. It is generally better to have a man at the head of a department composed of both men and women employees."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q17R>
/caption = "17. A husband should not feel uncomfortable if his wife earns a larger salary than he does."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q18R>
/caption = "18. It is all right for women to hold local political offices."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q19>
/caption = "19. If a male student and a female student are equally qualified for a certain scholarship; it should be awarded to the male student on the grounds that he has greater 'career potential'."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q20R>
/caption = "20. The use of profane or obscene language by a woman is no more objectionable than the same usage by a man."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>


<radiobuttons q21R>
/caption = "21. It is certainly acceptable for boys, as well as girls, to play with dolls."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q22>
/caption = "22. Girls should primarily be counseled to enter 'feminine' vocations such as nursing, public school teaching, library science, etc."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q23R>
/caption = "23. Women should not feel inhibited about competing in any form of athletics."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q24R>
/caption = "24. Parents should encourage just as much independence in their daughters as in their sons."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q25R>
/caption = "25. Women should be able to compete with men for jobs that have traditionally belonged to men, such as telephone lineman."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q26>
/caption = "26. It is O.K. for a wife to retain her maiden name if she wants to."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q27R>
/caption = "27. There is no reason why a woman should not be president of the United States."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q28>
/caption = "28. Career education for boys should have higher priority with parents and teachers than career education for girls."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q29>
/caption = "29. Even though a wife works outside the home, the husband should be the main breadwinner and the wife should have the responsibility for running the household."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q30>
/caption = "30. In elementary school, girls should wear dresses rather than slacks."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q31R>
/caption = "31. It is acceptable for a woman to become a member of the church clergy."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q32R>
/caption = "32. It is acceptable for women to hold important elected political offices in state and national government."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q33>
/caption = "33. It is not a good idea for a husband to stay home and care for the children while his wife employed full-time outside the home."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q34>
/caption = "34. The only reason girls need career education is that they may not marry or remain married."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q35R>
/caption = "35. There is no particular reason why a man should always offer his seat to a woman who is standing on a crowded bus."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q36R>
/caption = "36. Men should be able to compete with women for jobs that have traditionally belonged to women, such as telephone operator."
/ options = ("strongly~nagree", "moderately~nagree", "agree~nslightly more~nthan disagree", "disagree~nslightly more~nthan agree", "moderately~ndisagree", "strongly~ndisagree")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

